software.leonov.common.util.function

Interface CheckedComparator<T>

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface CheckedComparator<T>
    Mirror of the Comparator interface whose compare(T, T) method can throw a checked exception.

      • compare

        int compare(T left,
            T right)
     throws Exception
        Compares its two arguments for order.
        Parameters:
        left - the first argument
        right - the second argument
        Returns:
        a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the first argument is less than, equal to, or greater than the second
        Throws:
        Exception - if an error occurs

      • comparing

        static <T,U extends Comparable<? super U>> CheckedComparator<T> comparing(CheckedFunction<? super T,? extends U> function)
        Returns a comparator that applies the specified function to each element of type T and compares the results according to their natural ordering.

        The returned comparator is serializable if the specified function is also serializable.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of element to be compared
        U - the type of the result returned by the function
        Parameters:
        function - the function to apply
        Returns:
        a comparator that applies the specified function to each element of type T and compares the results according to their natural ordering

      • nullsFirst

        static <T> CheckedComparator<T> nullsFirst(CheckedComparator<? super T> comparator)
        Returns a comparator that considers null values to be less than non-null values. If both are non-null, the specified comparator is used to determine the order. If the specified comparator is null, then the returned comparator considers all non-null values to be equal.

        The returned comparator is serializable if the specified comparator is serializable.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements to be compared
        Parameters:
        comparator - the comparator to use for comparing non-null values
        Returns:
        a comparator that considers null values to be less than non-null values

      • nullsLast

        static <T> CheckedComparator<T> nullsLast(CheckedComparator<? super T> comparator)
        Returns a comparator that considers null values to be greater than non-null values. If both are non-null, the specified comparator is used to determine the order. If the specified comparator is null, then the returned comparator considers all non-null values to be equal.

        The returned comparator is serializable if the specified comparator is serializable.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements to be compared
        Parameters:
        comparator - the comparator to use for comparing non-null values
        Returns:
        a comparator that considers null values to be greater than non-null values

      • thenComparing

        default CheckedComparator<T> thenComparing(CheckedComparator<? super T> other)
        Returns a composed comparator which uses this comparator, followed by the other comparator if this comparator returns a zero result.

        Parameters:
